As we progress East through upstate New York, the terrain is changing quite rapidly in line with our progress towards&nbsp;New England. James described Little Falls&nbsp;as somewhat reminiscent of a small northern industrial town (in a good sort of way). We have hills again and the roadkill has changed from predominantly deer and raccoons to turtles and beavers (there&rsquo;s a lot of water around here).






James and Chris roll into Little Falls 'three-legged', tailed closely by Dirk



We continued to take it easy today in the hope that James' thigh will miraculously recover before Saturday&rsquo;s climbing if we treat it nicely until then. We averaged 14.2 mph for the ride and got a chance to talk with a different subset of the group as we rode along.
