Today we are on a 4 hour ferry crossing of Lake Michigan. The Internet service on the boat is apparently so poor as to make the hotels we&rsquo;ve been staying in feel as though they are at the very forefront of the digital revolution (in reality the hotel connectivity has on many days been worse than the 19.2kbps modem I had at home 20 years ago). Anyway, rather more constructively, I thought I&rsquo;d rattle this off before breakfast so James can post before we leave the hotel.
After spending 2,500 miles in the saddle I&rsquo;ve had a certain amount of time to develop coping strategies for dealing with self inflicted pain. James has been working on a hypothesis around the optimum pedalling speed to minimise total pain integrated over time. Sadly his preliminary draft did not pass the exacting peer review standards for this publication so here&rsquo;s something less scientific while he refines his thesis.&nbsp;
